# Build context for e2e/distributed/Dockerfile.dist is THIS dir (e2e/) — the
# common ancestor of econ/ and distributed/, so both COPY subtrees resolve. Trim
# everything the image does NOT COPY so the remote-builder upload stays small.
#
# Only builds that use e2e/ as their context read this file. The single-machine
# arm builds use a subdir context (e2e/econ, e2e/reference/codex, e2e/reference/claude)
# and read their OWN per-arm .dockerignore, so this file does not affect them.
#
# KEEP: econ/local-docker/{run-benchmark.py,Dockerfile.*,context (incl. vendor/)},
#       econ/{report.py,econ-telemetry.py,econ-tier-cost.py}, distributed/**.

**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.log
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/node_modules
**/.unerr
**/.DS_Store

# heavy per-run artifacts (never COPYed into the image)
**/out/
**/results/
**/reports/
**/logs/
**/grading/
**/*.tgz

# other arms are not part of the econ fleet image
reference/claude/
reference/codex/

# EXCEPTION: the claude arm's local-docker/ IS baked into the shared fleet image
# (distributed/Dockerfile.dist: `COPY reference/claude/local-docker
# /work/claude/local-docker`). Re-include it — run-benchmark.py, litellm_cost.py,
# cost_report.py, Dockerfile.*, and context/ incl. the vendored toolbox `.tgz`
# payload. These negations come AFTER both `reference/claude/` AND `**/*.tgz`
# above, so last-match-wins keeps the subtree (same technique as the
# dot-opencode/node_modules carve-out below).
!reference/claude/local-docker
!reference/claude/local-docker/**
# ...but keep local run scratch OUT of the image (re-excluded after the negation,
# so last-match-wins drops them again — scoped to the claude subtree only).
reference/claude/local-docker/results/
reference/claude/local-docker/logs/
reference/claude/local-docker/**/__pycache__/
reference/claude/local-docker/*.json

# EXCEPTION to the `**/node_modules` rule above: the econ toolbox vendors econ's
# `.opencode/` as `vendor/dot-opencode/`, and its `.opencode/tool/*.ts` project
# tools `import "@opencode-ai/plugin"` — a workspace dep that lives ONLY under
# `.opencode/node_modules/`. If it's stripped, opencode aborts the whole session
# at startup (UnknownError → econ exit=1, 0 turns, empty patch). Re-include just
# THIS node_modules tree (all other node_modules stay excluded to keep uploads
# small). Negations must come AFTER `**/node_modules` (last match wins).
!**/dot-opencode/node_modules
!**/dot-opencode/node_modules/**
